data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## Flowise Workflow Management Test — VAL-06\n\n### Executive Summary\n\n**The `VAL-06-Test-Flow` chatflow could not be created.** Flowise reports healthy on its local health endpoint, but all authenticated CRUD operations fail with **401 Unauthorized** due to missing OBO token forwarding. This is a **persistent, known defect** — identical to the previous test session on `2026-02-20T22:01Z`.\n\n---\n\n### Step-by-Step Results\n\n| Step | Operation | Tool | Status | Detail |\n|:----:|-----------|------|:------:|--------|\n| 1 | **Health check** | `flowise_health_check` | ✅ | Healthy — `2026-02-21T00:34:49.483590` |\n| 2 | **List chatflows** | `flowise_list_chatflows` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — No authentication token provided` |\n| 3 | **List nodes** | `flowise_list_nodes` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — No authentication token provided` |\n| 4a | **Create chatflow** (template) | `flowise_create_chatflow` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — No authentication token provided` |\n| 4b | **Create chatflow** (from_template) | `flowise_create_from_template` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — identical failure` |\n| 4c | **Create chatflow** (advanced) | `flowise_create_chatflow_advanced` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized — identical failure` |\n\n**Supplemental probes (unauthenticated endpoints — all succeeded):**\n\n| Probe | Status | Detail |\n|-------|:------:|--------|\n| **Creation guide** | ✅ | 5 templates, `chatOpenAgentic` patterns returned |\n| **List templates** | ✅ | 5 templates confirmed (`llm_chain` target available) |\n| **Framework status** | ⚠️ | Flowise marked **unhealthy** at the API gateway level |\n\n---\n\n### Health Signal Contradiction\n\n| Source | Flowise Status | Endpoint |\n|--------|:--------------:|----------|\n| `flowise_health_check` | ✅ Healthy | Local internal ping |\n| `get_framework_status` | ❌ Unhealthy | `http://openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace` |\n\nThe health check is a **false positive** — it validates the proxy process is running, not that the authenticated API path is functional.\n\n---\n\n### What Was Attempted for VAL-06-Test-Flow\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| **Name** | `VAL-06-Test-Flow` |\n| **Template** | `llm_chain` (Simple LLM with custom prompt) |\n| **Model** | `chatOpenAgentic` → `gemini-2.0-flash-001` |\n| **Deployed** | `true` |\n| **Public** | `true` |\n| **Category** | `validation` |\n| **Chatflow ID** | ❌ Not created — no ID assigned |\n\nThe `llm_chain` template would have provisioned:\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"VAL-06-Test-Flow (Intended Design)\",\n  \"layout\": \"horizontal\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"model\", \"label\": \"chatOpenAgentic\\ngemini-2.0-flash-001\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"primary\"},\n    {\"id\": \"prompt\", \"label\": \"Prompt\\nTemplate\", \"shape\": \"document\", \"color\": \"info\"},\n    {\"id\": \"chain\", \"label\": \"LLM Chain\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"success\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"model\", \"target\": \"chain\", \"label\": \"model\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"prompt\", \"target\": \"chain\", \"label\": \"prompt\", \"style\": \"solid\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n\nThis is the **same defect** observed in the previous session. The OBO (On-Behalf-Of) token is present in the MCP proxy context but is **not being forwarded** to outbound Flowise API requests.\n\n```\nMCP Proxy  ──[token present]──▶  Flowise API Gateway  ──[token MISSING]──▶  Flowise Backend\n                                    ↑\n                                    └── Returns 401\n```\n\n---\n\n### Recommendations\n\n| Priority | Action | Rationale |\n|:--------:|--------|-----------|\n| **P0** | **Fix OBO token forwarding** in MCP proxy → Flowise API path | All CRUD operations blocked across all 3 creation methods |\n| **P0** | **Fix Flowise workspace endpoint** — `get_framework_status` confirms it's unhealthy | Backend may be independently degraded |\n| **P1** | **Fix `flowise_health_check`** to probe authenticated endpoints | Currently gives false-positive \"healthy\" while API is down |\n| **P2** | **Re-run VAL-06** after P0 fix to complete lifecycle test | Steps 2–4 (plus update, test, analytics, delete) remain blocked |\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> **This is the 4th consecutive audit where Flowise CRUD operations fail with 401.** The OBO token forwarding defect has persisted across multiple sessions spanning `2026-02-20` to `2026-02-21`. This is a **P0 platform blocker** — no workflows can be created, listed, updated, or deleted through the MCP interface."}

